A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the State of Georgia so as to authorize the
2 General Assembly to provide by law for a homestead exemption for an additional 100
3 percent disabled veterans' homestead exemption for the full assessed value of a homestead
4 in certain circumstances; to authorize municipalities to seek supplementary funding to offset
5 lost revenue from the homestead exemption; to provide for a short title; to provide for
6 submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 This resolution shall be known and may be cited as the "Georgia Keys for Heroes
10 Amendment."
11 SECTION 2.
12 Article VII, Section II of the Constitution is amended by adding a new Paragraph to read as
13 follows:
14 "Paragraph VI. Additional disabled veterans' homestead exemption. (a) The General
15 Assembly shall provide by general law for the creation of an additional 100 percent
16 disabled veterans' homestead exemption for the full assessed value of a homestead upon
