17 a disabled veteran procuring a loan or otherwise financing the development of new
18 residential construction, obtaining or receiving a residential structure by inheritance, or
19 purchasing an existing residential structure, for the purpose of use as a primary residence.
20 (b) The general law provided for in subparagraph (a) of this Paragraph shall also include
21 authorization for municipalities to seek supplementary funding to offset lost revenue from
22 the homestead exemption provided for in subparagraph (a) of this Paragraph."
23 SECTION 3.
24 The above proposed amendment to the Constitution shall be published and submitted as
25 provided in Article X, Section I, Paragraph II of the Constitution. The ballot submitting the
26 above proposed amendment shall have written or printed thereon the following:
27 "( ) YES Shall the Constitution of Georgia be amended so as to authorize the General
28 Assembly to provide by general law for the creation of an additional 100
29 ( ) NO percent disabled veterans' homestead exemption for the full assessed value
30 of a homestead upon procuring a loan or otherwise financing the
31 development of new residential construction, obtaining or receiving a
32 residential structure by inheritance, or purchasing an existing residential
33 structure, for the purpose of use as a primary residence, and authorization
34 for municipalities to seek supplementary funding to offset lost revenue from
35 the homestead exemption?"
36 All persons desiring to vote in favor of ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "Yes."
37 All persons desiring to vote against ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "No." If
38 such amendment shall be ratified as provided in said Paragraph of the Constitution, it shall
39 become a part of the Constitution of this state.
